{
  "step_by_step_reasoning": "Chronological analysis of the architecture reveals two primary pipelines: Ingestion and Analysis/Notification. 1) Applications ingest data via Kinesis into a Fargate ingestion service. This service parses and stores raw data in Aurora and S3, with Glue processing ETL on S3 data. 2) A scheduler triggers an Analysis Fargate service to scope analysis and launch an EMR job. 3) The EMR job reads data from S3 and Aurora to run rules, generating violation events sent to EventBridge. 4) EventBridge queues violations to SQS, which are read and decorated by a Fargate decorator service, then emailed via SMTP. We separate Fargate into three nodes representing distinct services as described in the transcript.",
